==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intelligible
<hw>In*tel"li*gi*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[L.
<ets>intellegibilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>intelligible</ets>. See
<er>Intelligent</er>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being understood or
comprehended; <as>as, an <ex>intelligible</ex> account or description;
<ex>intelligible</ex> pronunciation, writing, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>intelligible</qex> forms of ancient poets.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Comprehensible; perspicuous; plain;
clear.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intelligibleness</ent>⟦br⟧
